# Pomodoro Timer Web Application Implementation Plan

Create a beautiful, dark-themed Pomodoro timer to help users stay focused.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - The project will be initialized in `C:\Users\yunsa\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\pomodoro-timer`.
> - I will use **React (JavaScript)** to keep it simple and friendly for beginners, as per the Kodari persona's goal.
> - **Tailwind CSS** will be used for styling to achieve the requested "soothing dark theme."

## Proposed Changes

### [NEW] Project Initialization
- Run `npx create-vite@latest pomodoro-timer --template react`
- Install dependencies: `react`, `react-dom`
- Install Tailwind CSS: `tailwindcss`, `postcss`, `autoprefixer`

### [NEW] Configuration
- `tailwind.config.js`: Configure content paths and dark mode.
- `src/index.css`: Add Tailwind directives.

### [NEW] Components
- `src/App.jsx`: Main layout and state management for the timer.
- `src/components/Timer.jsx`: Visual display of the clock and session type.
- `src/components/Controls.jsx`: Start, Pause, and Reset buttons.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Start the timer and verify it counts down from 25:00.
- Check if it automatically switches to a 5-minute break after the focus session.
- Test the Pause and Reset buttons.
- Resize the browser to ensure the UI is responsive.
